WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:19.000
Tails from the Thousand and One Nights

00:19.000 --> 00:23.000
Copyright Black Cat Publishing

00:30.000 --> 00:46.000
The Story of Sharaya and Sharazad, His Vizier's Daughter

00:46.000 --> 00:49.000
Part 1

00:49.000 --> 00:57.000
There were once two kings called Sharaya and Shahzaman. They were brothers.

00:57.000 --> 01:04.000
Sharaya was an important king. He ruled all of Persia, India and China.

01:04.000 --> 01:10.000
Shahzaman, his younger brother, was the king of Samarkand.

01:10.000 --> 01:13.000
One day, Sharaya said to his Vizier,

01:13.000 --> 01:20.000
I'd like to see my brother. Go to his palace in Samarkand and invite him to India.

01:20.000 --> 01:29.000
The Vizier, who had two daughters, Sharazad and Dinasad, made preparations for his long journey.

01:29.000 --> 01:39.000
He and his servants travelled day and night. When they arrived in Samarkand, the king greeted the Vizier warmly.

01:39.000 --> 01:45.000
Welcome to Samarkand. He said, tell me, how is my brother?

01:45.000 --> 01:52.000
He is well your majesty, but he'd like to see you again. He told me to invite you to India.

01:52.000 --> 01:56.000
I'll prepare for the journey immediately. Said the king.

01:56.000 --> 02:03.000
You and your servants can put your tents in the big field outside the city walls. Wait for me there.

02:03.000 --> 02:09.000
One evening, ten days later, Shahzaman arrived at the Vizier's camp.

02:09.000 --> 02:16.000
We'll start our journey early tomorrow morning. He told the Vizier, and then he went to bed.

02:16.000 --> 02:20.000
At midnight, the Vizier received a visit from the king.

02:20.000 --> 02:27.000
I'd like to say goodbye to my wife one more time, he said. I'm going to return to the city.

02:28.000 --> 02:34.000
Shahzaman rode back to the palace and went straight to his wife's bedroom and opened the door.

02:34.000 --> 02:42.000
She was there in bed, but she wasn't alone. She was with one of the kitchen boys.

02:42.000 --> 02:49.000
Shahzaman was very angry. He took out his sword and killed both of them.

02:49.000 --> 02:52.000
Then he returned to the camp.

02:52.000 --> 02:59.000
The next day, the king, the Vizier and all their servants left Samakan.

02:59.000 --> 03:06.000
They traveled for many days and nights. Finally, they arrived at the royal palace in India.

03:06.000 --> 03:12.000
Shahraya came out to greet his brother. He was very happy to see him again.

03:12.000 --> 03:19.000
He gave him clean clothes, food and drink. He gave him a palace to stay in.

03:19.000 --> 03:26.000
That palace will be your home here. He said, but you must come and see me every day.

03:26.000 --> 03:34.000
The two brothers spent the days pleasantly. They talked, played chess and walked in the gardens.

03:34.000 --> 03:42.000
But Shahzaman thought about his wife all the time. He was very sad. He stopped eating.

03:42.000 --> 03:46.000
He became thin and pale. His brother was worried.

03:46.000 --> 03:52.000
Perhaps he wants to go home, he thought. I'll send him back soon.

03:52.000 --> 04:00.000
One morning, Shahraya said, I'm going hunting in the forest, brother. I'll be away for ten days.

04:00.000 --> 04:03.000
Would you like to come with me before you go back to Samakan?

04:03.000 --> 04:09.000
Thank you, brother. But I'm tired. You go. I'll stay here.

04:09.000 --> 04:16.000
Replied Shahzaman. He sat at his bedroom window all day.

04:16.000 --> 04:23.000
He thought about his wife and felt sad. He could see the garden of his brother's palace from his window.

04:23.000 --> 04:31.000
It was very beautiful. There were trees and flowers. There were peacocks. There was a fountain.

04:31.000 --> 04:37.000
There were also two people in the garden that day. A man and a woman.

04:37.000 --> 04:42.000
They were kissing and laughing. Shahzaman looked at them carefully.

04:42.000 --> 04:48.000
The woman was his brother's wife, and the man was one of her slaves.

04:48.000 --> 04:58.000
Shahzaman was very surprised. He thought, my brother's more important than me, but he's unlucky with his wife too.

04:58.000 --> 05:03.000
And he began to feel better. He started eating again.

05:07.000 --> 05:10.000
Part two.

05:10.000 --> 05:18.000
When Shahraya came back from hunting and saw his brother, he said, you are well now, brother. I am happy.

05:18.000 --> 05:22.000
Tell me, why were you so sad before?

05:22.000 --> 05:26.000
Shahzaman told him about his own wife and the kitchen boy.

05:26.000 --> 05:31.000
Then he told Shahraya about his wife and her slave.

05:31.000 --> 05:36.000
Shahraya loved his wife very much. He said, I don't believe you.

05:36.000 --> 05:40.000
My wife's a good woman.

05:40.000 --> 05:42.000
Go hunting again tomorrow.

05:42.000 --> 05:43.000
Said his brother.

05:43.000 --> 05:49.000
But come back secretly in the evening. Then you'll see them.

05:49.000 --> 05:57.000
So the next day, Shahraya went to the forest. When it was dark, he returned on foot.

05:57.000 --> 06:03.000
In the morning, the king went to his brother's room and looked down into the garden.

06:03.000 --> 06:08.000
His wife and her slave were there. They were kissing and laughing.

06:08.000 --> 06:13.000
Shahraya was very angry. He immediately called his vizier.

06:13.000 --> 06:15.000
Kill them both, he said.

06:15.000 --> 06:17.000
Oh brother.

06:17.000 --> 06:18.000
Said Shahzaman.

06:18.000 --> 06:23.000
There are no good women in the world. They are all bad.

06:23.000 --> 06:25.000
You are right, brother.

06:25.000 --> 06:29.000
The king replied sadly.

06:29.000 --> 06:34.000
Soon after this, Shahzaman went back to Samarkand.

06:34.000 --> 06:39.000
One night, a month or two later, Shahraya said to his vizier,

06:39.000 --> 06:43.000
I want a new wife. Go and find one for me.

06:43.000 --> 06:50.000
The vizier found a girl. He took her to the king's bedroom and Shahraya married her.

06:50.000 --> 06:55.000
In the morning, he said to his vizier, now kill her.

06:56.000 --> 07:00.000
The next night, he told his vizier to find him another girl.

07:00.000 --> 07:04.000
The vizier found one and Shahraya married her.

07:04.000 --> 07:07.000
In the morning, he told his vizier to kill her.

07:07.000 --> 07:14.000
Every night, the king married a different girl, and in the morning, his vizier killed her.

07:14.000 --> 07:18.000
The people in the kingdom became very angry with the king.

07:18.000 --> 07:21.000
They didn't like losing their daughters.

07:22.000 --> 07:26.000
One day, Shahraya said, the vizier's daughter said,

07:26.000 --> 07:32.000
Father, I'd like to marry the king. I want to try to help our people.

07:32.000 --> 07:39.000
She was a very intelligent girl. She read and studied a lot and knew many things.

07:39.000 --> 07:42.000
But when her father heard this, he was angry.

07:42.000 --> 07:49.000
His silly girl. The king will spend one night with you, and then, in the morning, I'll have to kill you.

07:49.000 --> 07:52.000
I want to help our people, Father.

07:52.000 --> 07:58.000
Shahraya said, I have a plan. Please, take me to the king.

07:58.000 --> 08:02.000
The vizier was sad, but he took her to the king.

08:02.000 --> 08:08.000
Later that night, when the king and Shahraya were in bed, she started crying.

08:08.000 --> 08:12.000
Why are you crying? Ask the king.

08:12.000 --> 08:17.000
I'd like to see my sister one more time before I die.

08:17.000 --> 08:22.000
She said, so the king sent for her sister, Dinazad.

08:22.000 --> 08:27.000
When she arrived, she went and sat next to Shahraya'sad and said,

08:27.000 --> 08:33.000
Sister, tell me a story, please. The night will pass more pleasantly.

08:33.000 --> 08:37.000
Shahraya'sad began to tell a story.

08:37.000 --> 08:43.000
Dinazad listened. The king wasn't tired, so he listened too.

08:43.000 --> 08:47.000
She told one story and started another one.

08:47.000 --> 08:52.000
But when she saw the first light of morning through the window, she stopped.

08:52.000 --> 08:58.000
I must know the end of that story, said the king. You must finish it tomorrow.

08:58.000 --> 09:02.000
So her father didn't have to kill her in the morning.

09:02.000 --> 09:08.000
The next night, Shahraya'sad finished the story and started another one.

09:09.000 --> 09:15.000
She continued to tell the king's stories for one thousand and one nights.

09:15.000 --> 09:19.000
During this time, they had three children.

09:19.000 --> 09:26.000
Then one day, the king said, You are a good and intelligent woman, Shahraya'sad.

09:26.000 --> 09:30.000
I will never kill you. You will be my queen.

09:30.000 --> 09:35.000
And they lived happily together for the rest of their lives.

09:35.000 --> 09:43.000
The Enchanted Horse, Part 1

09:43.000 --> 09:47.000
It was new year in the city of Shahraya's in Persia.

09:47.000 --> 09:53.000
The city's square was full of people. The king and his family were there too.

09:53.000 --> 09:59.000
There was music and dancing. There were fire eaters and snake charmers.

09:59.000 --> 10:04.000
And of course, there was a lot of delicious food and drink.

10:04.000 --> 10:08.000
Suddenly, an Indian man appeared in front of the king.

10:08.000 --> 10:14.000
He had a beautiful horse with him. It was made of black wood.

10:14.000 --> 10:17.000
The Indian spoke to the king.

10:17.000 --> 10:22.000
Your Majesty, this is a very special horse.

10:22.000 --> 10:23.000
Really?

10:23.000 --> 10:24.000
Said the king.

10:24.000 --> 10:31.000
Why is it special? What can it do? It can fly your Majesty.

10:31.000 --> 10:38.000
When I press this little button on its neck, it flies up into the air and takes me where I want to go.

10:38.000 --> 10:42.000
Your horse is certainly a very special horse.

10:42.000 --> 10:43.000
Said the king.

10:43.000 --> 10:48.000
I'd like to have it for myself. I'll sell it to you, your Majesty.

10:48.000 --> 10:50.000
And what's the price?

10:50.000 --> 10:51.000
Ask the king.

10:51.000 --> 10:56.000
Your daughter. I want to marry your daughter.

10:56.000 --> 10:57.000
Reply the Indian.

10:57.000 --> 11:00.000
That's a very high price for a horse.

11:00.000 --> 11:05.000
It isn't a high price for a horse that can fly your Majesty.

11:05.000 --> 11:09.000
Try it, and you'll see for yourself.

11:09.000 --> 11:12.000
Let my son, Prince Feroos, try the horse.

11:12.000 --> 11:14.000
Said the king.

11:14.000 --> 11:21.000
Prince Feroos immediately jumped on the horse's back and pressed the button on its neck.

11:21.000 --> 11:26.000
The horse flew up into the air, into the clouds, and disappeared.

11:26.000 --> 11:29.000
The king was very angry.

11:29.000 --> 11:32.000
Where is my son? He shouted. Bring him back.

11:32.000 --> 11:34.000
I can't.

11:34.000 --> 11:36.000
Reply the Indian.

11:36.000 --> 11:40.000
The king ordered his guards to put the Indian in prison.

11:40.000 --> 11:45.000
My guards will kill you if Prince Feroos isn't back in three months.

11:45.000 --> 11:46.000
He said.

11:46.000 --> 11:51.000
Meanwhile, the horse and the prince flew higher and higher.

11:51.000 --> 11:56.000
The prince was happy. He enjoyed flying on the horse.

11:56.000 --> 11:59.000
Then it began to get dark.

11:59.000 --> 12:03.000
It's late, he thought. I must land.

12:03.000 --> 12:08.000
He looked carefully at the horse's neck and saw another little button.

12:08.000 --> 12:15.000
He pressed it and the horse landed on the terrace of a beautiful white palace.

12:15.000 --> 12:18.000
He got off and looked around him.

12:18.000 --> 12:22.000
There was a small door in the corner of the terrace.

12:22.000 --> 12:25.000
He opened it and saw some stairs.

12:25.000 --> 12:29.000
He went down them and into a long hall with many doors.

12:29.000 --> 12:34.000
There was a light under one of them, so he opened it.

12:34.000 --> 12:38.000
Six guards were asleep on the floor.

12:38.000 --> 12:43.000
The light was coming from a lamp in another room behind a curtain.

12:43.000 --> 12:48.000
Prince Feroos moved the curtain and looked in.

12:48.000 --> 12:53.000
He saw a big sofa and some women asleep around it.

12:53.000 --> 12:57.000
On the sofa, there was a very beautiful girl.

12:57.000 --> 13:03.000
Prince Feroos touched her arm gently and she opened her eyes.

13:03.000 --> 13:05.000
Don't be afraid, he said.

13:05.000 --> 13:13.000
I'm the son of the king of Persia. I don't want to hurt you. I'm lost and in danger.

13:13.000 --> 13:17.000
I'm the daughter of the Sultan of Bengal, said the princess.

13:17.000 --> 13:20.000
Don't worry, you're safe in my palace.

13:20.000 --> 13:24.000
Then she called one of her maids and said to her,

13:24.000 --> 13:29.000
Give the prince some food and a bed. We'll talk in the morning.

13:29.000 --> 13:34.000
The princess thought about the handsome young prince all night.

13:34.000 --> 13:41.000
The next morning, she put on her most beautiful dress and finest jewels and went out into the garden.

13:41.000 --> 13:44.000
Prince Feroos was there.

13:44.000 --> 13:46.000
He told her his story.

13:46.000 --> 13:50.000
Dear princess, I must return home to my father, he said.

13:50.000 --> 13:53.000
He doesn't know that I'm here.

13:53.000 --> 13:56.000
The princess was sad when she heard this.

13:56.000 --> 13:59.000
Can't you stay for just two more days?

13:59.000 --> 14:00.000
She asked.

14:00.000 --> 14:06.000
I'm lonely here. My maids and the palace guards are my only companions.

14:06.000 --> 14:14.000
The prince looked at the sad face of the beautiful princess of Bengal and decided to stay.

14:15.000 --> 14:18.000
Part two.

14:18.000 --> 14:23.000
The days became weeks and the weeks became months.

14:23.000 --> 14:28.000
The prince and the princess fell in love. They wanted to get married.

14:28.000 --> 14:33.000
One day, Prince Feroos said, I must go back to Persia.

14:33.000 --> 14:39.000
My father's waiting for me. Come with me. We can get married and live there.

14:40.000 --> 14:42.000
The princess agreed.

14:42.000 --> 14:49.000
So that night after dark, they both got on the horses back and flew across the skies to Persia.

14:49.000 --> 14:53.000
They landed in the garden of a small house outside the city.

14:53.000 --> 14:58.000
Stay here tonight. He told her, I'll come for you tomorrow.

14:58.000 --> 15:03.000
Then Prince Feroos went to his father's palace.

15:03.000 --> 15:07.000
The king was very happy to see his son again.

15:07.000 --> 15:10.000
He told the guards to bring the Indian to him.

15:10.000 --> 15:14.000
Take your horse and never enter my kingdom again.

15:14.000 --> 15:16.000
He said to him.

15:16.000 --> 15:20.000
The Indian was angry with the king because he put him in prison.

15:20.000 --> 15:25.000
And he was angry with Prince Feroos because he took his horse.

15:25.000 --> 15:28.000
He wanted his revenge.

15:28.000 --> 15:33.000
The palace guards told the Indian that his horse was in a house outside the city.

15:33.000 --> 15:36.000
So he went there the next day.

15:36.000 --> 15:43.000
A servant answered the door. The Indian said, the prince is waiting for the princess.

15:43.000 --> 15:46.000
She must come with me to the palace.

15:46.000 --> 15:52.000
A few moments later the princess was on the horse behind the Indian.

15:52.000 --> 15:56.000
They flew up into the air and in the direction of the palace.

15:56.000 --> 16:00.000
The prince and the king looked up and saw them.

16:00.000 --> 16:05.000
But the horse didn't land there. It flew over the palace and disappeared.

16:05.000 --> 16:08.000
The prince was afraid.

16:08.000 --> 16:13.000
The princess is in danger and must go and look for her immediately.

16:13.000 --> 16:15.000
He said to his father.

16:15.000 --> 16:19.000
The horse took the Indian and the princess to India.

16:19.000 --> 16:24.000
It landed in a forest near the Sultan of Kashmir's palace.

16:24.000 --> 16:27.000
The princess started shouting for help.

16:27.000 --> 16:32.000
The Sultan was hunting in the forest that day and he heard her.

16:32.000 --> 16:35.000
Perhaps that girl is in danger.

16:35.000 --> 16:38.000
He thought, I must go and save her.

16:38.000 --> 16:43.000
When he saw the Indian he pulled out his sword and killed him.

16:43.000 --> 16:49.000
Then he put the princess on his horse and they rode back to his palace.

16:49.000 --> 16:54.000
Earlier the next morning the princess heard a lot of noise outside her room.

16:54.000 --> 16:55.000
What's that noise?

16:55.000 --> 16:57.000
She asked a maid.

16:57.000 --> 17:00.000
The servants are preparing for your wedding.

17:00.000 --> 17:02.000
Tomorrow you will marry the Sultan.

17:02.000 --> 17:04.000
She said.

17:04.000 --> 17:06.000
The princess was horrified.

17:06.000 --> 17:08.000
I must do something.

17:08.000 --> 17:09.000
She thought.

17:09.000 --> 17:13.000
I can't marry the Sultan. I don't love him.

17:13.000 --> 17:18.000
She started shouting and crying and pulling her hair.

17:18.000 --> 17:21.000
The maid was afraid. She went to the Sultan and said,

17:21.000 --> 17:26.000
The princess is ill. She can't marry you tomorrow.

17:26.000 --> 17:28.000
Look after her. He said.

17:28.000 --> 17:32.000
And we'll get married when she's better.

17:32.000 --> 17:36.000
But weeks and months passed.

17:36.000 --> 17:41.000
Many doctors came to see the princess but she didn't get better.

17:41.000 --> 17:47.000
Then one day a young doctor from Persia arrived at the palace gate.

17:47.000 --> 17:49.000
It was Prince Farus.

17:49.000 --> 17:52.000
The princess was very happy to see him.

17:52.000 --> 17:54.000
We must escape.

17:54.000 --> 17:56.000
The prince told her. And I have a plan.

17:56.000 --> 18:01.000
But first he must stop crying and smile at the Sultan.

18:01.000 --> 18:06.000
So the princess stopped crying and smiled at the Sultan.

18:06.000 --> 18:08.000
He was very happy.

18:08.000 --> 18:11.000
You are a very good doctor.

18:11.000 --> 18:13.000
He said to Prince Farus.

18:13.000 --> 18:17.000
The princess is well now. You can go home.

18:17.000 --> 18:19.000
She isn't completely well.

18:19.000 --> 18:23.000
The prince said the enchanted horse put a magic spell on her.

18:23.000 --> 18:29.000
Bring the horse and the princess to the square this afternoon and I'll take away the spell.

18:29.000 --> 18:34.000
Tell all the people in the town to come and watch.

18:34.000 --> 18:39.000
At four o'clock that afternoon the city square was full of people.

18:39.000 --> 18:43.000
The Sultan and the princess were there too.

18:43.000 --> 18:48.000
When the guards brought the horse, Prince Farus made four fires around it.

18:48.000 --> 18:54.000
He said some strange words and threw some powder into the fires.

18:54.000 --> 19:00.000
Suddenly there was a lot of smoke. It was impossible to see anything.

19:00.000 --> 19:08.000
At that moment Prince Farus and the princess jumped on the horse's back and the horse flew up into the air.

19:08.000 --> 19:13.000
Soon they arrived at the king's palace in Shiraz.

19:13.000 --> 19:18.000
The king and his people were very happy to see them.

19:18.000 --> 19:27.000
The next day the prince and the princess got married and they lived happily for the rest of their lives.

19:29.000 --> 19:33.000
Ali Baba and the Forty Thieves.

19:33.000 --> 19:36.000
Part 1.

19:36.000 --> 19:40.000
Kazim and Ali Baba were brothers.

19:40.000 --> 19:43.000
They lived in a city in Persia.

19:43.000 --> 19:50.000
Kazim was rich. He had a shop. He bought and sold gold there.

19:50.000 --> 19:57.000
Ali Baba was poor. He collected wood in the forest and sold it in the city.

19:57.000 --> 20:05.000
One day while he was collecting wood, Ali Baba heard the sound of horses hooves in the distance.

20:05.000 --> 20:08.000
Who's coming here? He asked himself.

20:08.000 --> 20:13.000
Perhaps they are thieves and want to steal my wood. I'll hide in this tree.

20:13.000 --> 20:18.000
He quickly climbed up the tree and hid in the branches.

20:18.000 --> 20:28.000
The horsemen arrived. Ali Baba counted forty men. They were big and strong and they had black beards.

20:28.000 --> 20:31.000
Each of them had a heavy saddlebag.

20:31.000 --> 20:34.000
I was right. They are thieves.

20:34.000 --> 20:37.000
I thought Ali Baba.

20:37.000 --> 20:45.000
There was a big rock near the tree. The captain of the band of thieves went up to it and said,

20:45.000 --> 20:51.000
open sesame. Immediately a large door opened.

20:51.000 --> 20:57.000
They all went inside and the door in the rock closed behind them.

20:57.000 --> 21:01.000
The captain and his men stayed in the cave for a long time.

21:01.000 --> 21:09.000
Ali Baba began to get tired. Suddenly the door opened and they came out.

21:09.000 --> 21:16.000
Their saddlebags were empty now. The captain said, shot sesame!

21:16.000 --> 21:20.000
And the door closed and disappeared.

21:20.000 --> 21:24.000
Then they got on their horses and rode away.

21:25.000 --> 21:28.000
Ali Baba climbed down the tree.

21:28.000 --> 21:34.000
I'll try those magic words. Perhaps there is treasure in the cave, he thought.

21:34.000 --> 21:36.000
Open sesame!

21:36.000 --> 21:40.000
He said, and the door in the rock opened.

21:40.000 --> 21:44.000
It wasn't very dark inside the cave, so he could see well.

21:44.000 --> 21:51.000
There were bags of precious tunes, rubies, sapphires and emeralds.

21:51.000 --> 21:55.000
There were beautiful carpets and silk cloth.

21:55.000 --> 22:00.000
There were chests full of gold and silver coins.

22:00.000 --> 22:08.000
Ali Baba went back to his donkeys, took his bags and went inside the cave.

22:08.000 --> 22:12.000
He filled his bags as quickly as he could with coins.

22:12.000 --> 22:16.000
Then he hid them under some wood on his donkeys.

22:16.000 --> 22:18.000
Shut sesame!

22:18.000 --> 22:21.000
He said, and the door closed.

22:21.000 --> 22:28.000
When he arrived home and showed his wife the gold coins, her eyes became as big as dinner plates.

22:28.000 --> 22:30.000
She started counting them.

22:30.000 --> 22:32.000
Stupid woman!

22:32.000 --> 22:33.000
Said Ali Baba.

22:33.000 --> 22:41.000
Go and get the scales from your sister-in-law. We must weigh them. There are too many to count.

22:41.000 --> 22:49.000
Ali Baba's wife went to Kazim's house and asked for the scales. Her sister-in-law was surprised.

22:49.000 --> 22:51.000
Ali Baba is a poor man.

22:51.000 --> 22:55.000
She thought, what does he want to weigh?

22:55.000 --> 23:03.000
Before giving the scales to Ali Baba's wife, she took the cup and put some wax on the bottom of it.

23:03.000 --> 23:10.000
When Ali Baba's wife brought the scales back the next day, her sister-in-law looked at the cup carefully.

23:10.000 --> 23:14.000
There was a gold coin sticking to the wax.

23:14.000 --> 23:17.000
That evening, she said to her husband,

23:17.000 --> 23:26.000
You think you are rich, but Ali Baba has more gold than you. He doesn't count his money. He weighs it.

23:26.000 --> 23:32.000
Kazim didn't sleep that night. He thought about his brother's gold.

23:32.000 --> 23:38.000
The next morning, he went to Ali Baba's house and showed him the gold coin.

23:38.000 --> 23:48.000
He said, Brother, you say you are poor, but I know that you weigh your gold. My wife found this coin in the cup of the scales.

23:48.000 --> 23:50.000
Where did you get it?

23:50.000 --> 23:57.000
Ali Baba was an honest man, so he told Kazim about the cave in the forest.

23:57.000 --> 24:02.000
When he heard about the treasure, Kazim wanted some of the gold too.

24:02.000 --> 24:13.000
Without saying anything to his wife or Ali Baba, he took ten donkeys, each with two bags, and went to the forest.

24:13.000 --> 24:21.000
He found the rock and said the magic words, Open Sesame! The door opened.

24:21.000 --> 24:28.000
He went inside the cave and immediately started filling his bags with coins and jewels.

24:28.000 --> 24:33.000
While he was filling the last bag, he heard the sound of horses hooves outside.

24:33.000 --> 24:39.000
The thieves, he thought, What shall I do? They'll kill me. Where can I hide?

24:39.000 --> 24:46.000
He looked around the cave, but at that moment, the door opened and the captain came in.

24:46.000 --> 24:52.000
Kazim tried to escape, but the captain caught him and killed him with his sword.

24:52.000 --> 24:55.000
Perhaps other people know about the cave.

24:55.000 --> 24:59.000
We'll leave his body here as a warning to them.

24:59.000 --> 25:01.000
Send the captain.

25:01.000 --> 25:08.000
He cut Kazim's body into four pieces and put them around the door of the cave.

25:08.000 --> 25:19.000
Then, after putting the gold and silver back in the chests, the captain and the thieves left.

25:20.000 --> 25:22.000
Part two.

25:23.000 --> 25:28.000
Kazim's wife was worried about her husband. He was late for dinner.

25:28.000 --> 25:30.000
She went to see Ali Baba.

25:30.000 --> 25:32.000
Brother-in-law?

25:32.000 --> 25:33.000
She said.

25:33.000 --> 25:38.000
I'm worried about Kazim. He's very late. Please go and find him.

25:38.000 --> 25:41.000
Tell him that I'm waiting to serve dinner.

25:41.000 --> 25:46.000
Ali Baba knew that his brother liked gold. He thought,

25:46.000 --> 25:51.000
perhaps Kazim is in the cave. I'll go there first.

25:51.000 --> 25:59.000
When he opened the door of the cave and saw the pieces of his brother's body around the door, he was afraid.

25:59.000 --> 26:01.000
The thieves will kill me next.

26:01.000 --> 26:04.000
He thought, I must get out of here quickly.

26:04.000 --> 26:10.000
Before he left, he filled his bags with gold and put them on his donkeys.

26:10.000 --> 26:17.000
Then he put Kazim's body in another bag and rode back to his sister-in-law's house.

26:17.000 --> 26:23.000
One of Kazim's slaves opened the door. Her name was Mortjana.

26:23.000 --> 26:30.000
Ali Baba gave her the bag with Kazim's body and some instructions about the funeral.

26:30.000 --> 26:33.000
Then he went to see his sister-in-law.

26:33.000 --> 26:36.000
She cried when she heard that her husband was dead.

26:36.000 --> 26:45.000
Sister-in-law, he said, we're in danger. Nobody must know how Kazim died. It must be a secret.

26:45.000 --> 26:48.000
Then he told her about the treasure and the thieves.

26:48.000 --> 26:51.000
Don't worry, he said.

26:51.000 --> 26:59.000
I'm rich now. I'll marry you and look after you. My wife and I will come and live in this house.

26:59.000 --> 27:04.000
When Kazim's wife heard this, she stopped crying.

27:05.000 --> 27:14.000
Mortjana was a clever girl. She understood Ali Baba's instructions about Kazim's funeral and she knew what to do.

27:14.000 --> 27:19.000
She went to see Baba Mustafa, the shoemaker in the market.

27:19.000 --> 27:26.000
She gave him a gold coin and said, I have a special job for you Baba Mustafa.

27:26.000 --> 27:30.000
Cover your eyes with this cloth and come with me.

27:30.000 --> 27:35.000
He was a poor man, so he took the coin and covered his eyes.

27:35.000 --> 27:41.000
Mortjana took him through the streets of Baghdad to Kazim's house.

27:41.000 --> 27:45.000
When he took off the cloth, he was in a dark room.

27:45.000 --> 27:48.000
So those pieces together again?

27:48.000 --> 27:53.000
She said to him and pointed to the four pieces of Kazim's body on a table.

27:53.000 --> 27:56.000
Then make a bag for the body.

27:57.000 --> 28:00.000
Mustafa worked all day.

28:00.000 --> 28:10.000
When the body was in the bag, Mortjana gave Mustafa another gold coin, covered his eyes and took him back to his shop.

28:10.000 --> 28:16.000
Three days after Kazim's funeral, Ali Baba moved into his house.

28:16.000 --> 28:21.000
In the meantime, the thieves returned to the cave.

28:21.000 --> 28:25.000
Where's the body of that man? Where's our gold?

28:25.000 --> 28:28.000
They asked angrily.

28:28.000 --> 28:31.000
The captain said, someone knows the magic words.

28:31.000 --> 28:36.000
We must find him and kill him before he steals the rest of our treasure.

28:36.000 --> 28:42.000
He told his best man to dress himself as a merchant and go to the city.

28:42.000 --> 28:48.000
Come back when you find the man who knows the magic words, he said.

28:48.000 --> 28:54.000
It was early morning and still dark when the thief arrived in the market square.

28:54.000 --> 29:00.000
Only Mustafa was awake. He was sewing shoes outside his shop.

29:00.000 --> 29:02.000
How can you see to sew?

29:02.000 --> 29:05.000
Ask the thief. It's dark.

29:05.000 --> 29:09.000
I am old, but my eyes are still good.

29:09.000 --> 29:11.000
Replied Mustafa.

29:11.000 --> 29:17.000
Yesterday, I sewed four pieces of a body together in a dark room.

29:17.000 --> 29:22.000
Take me to that house and I'll give you these gold coins.

29:22.000 --> 29:24.000
Said the thief.

29:24.000 --> 29:27.000
Mustafa put the coins in his pocket.

29:27.000 --> 29:28.000
Follow me.

29:28.000 --> 29:35.000
He said. He had a good memory, so it wasn't difficult for him to remember the way.

29:35.000 --> 29:44.000
When they arrived at Ali Baba's house, the thief took out a piece of white chalk and put a cross on the door.

29:44.000 --> 29:49.000
Then he thanked Mustafa and rode back to the forest.

29:49.000 --> 29:53.000
Morjana returned home from the market.

29:53.000 --> 29:56.000
She was surprised to see the cross on the door.

29:56.000 --> 29:59.000
Perhaps someone wants to hurt my master?

29:59.000 --> 30:00.000
She thought.

30:00.000 --> 30:05.000
And she put a white cross on all the other doors in the street.

30:05.000 --> 30:11.000
When the captain arrived and saw that there were white crosses on all the doors, he was angry.

30:11.000 --> 30:17.000
He rode back to the forest and killed his best man.

30:17.000 --> 30:22.000
The next day, he sent his second best man to Mustafa.

30:22.000 --> 30:26.000
This time, the thief put a red cross on the door.

30:26.000 --> 30:32.000
Morjana saw the cross and put red crosses on all the other doors.

30:32.000 --> 30:39.000
When the captain arrived and saw that there were red crosses on all the doors, he was angrier than before.

30:39.000 --> 30:44.000
He rode back to the forest and killed his second best man.

30:44.000 --> 30:49.000
Tomorrow, I will go and find this man's house, he said.

30:49.000 --> 30:54.000
When he returned from the city, he called his men together.

30:54.000 --> 31:05.000
We must kill this man and take back our golden jewels, he said, and I have a plan.

31:05.000 --> 31:08.000
Part 3

31:08.000 --> 31:13.000
The captain told his men to bring him 38 big oil jars.

31:13.000 --> 31:20.000
He filled one of the jars with oil and told his men to climb into the others.

31:20.000 --> 31:23.000
Then he put the jars on donkeys.

31:23.000 --> 31:29.000
He dressed himself as a merchant and rode to Ali Baba's house.

31:29.000 --> 31:31.000
Morjana opened the door.

31:31.000 --> 31:34.000
I'm an oil merchant, he said.

31:34.000 --> 31:39.000
All the hotels in the city are full and it's late.

31:39.000 --> 31:43.000
Can the master of the house give me a bed for the night?

31:43.000 --> 31:46.000
Ali Baba was happy to help the merchant.

31:46.000 --> 31:51.000
Tell him to leave his jars downstairs, he said to Morjana.

31:51.000 --> 31:57.000
After dinner, the captain went downstairs and whispered to his men in the jars.

31:57.000 --> 32:04.000
When I say, it's time, break the jars and come upstairs.

32:04.000 --> 32:07.000
Then he went to bed.

32:07.000 --> 32:09.000
Morjana was in the kitchen.

32:09.000 --> 32:14.000
She wanted to make some soup, but she didn't have any oil.

32:14.000 --> 32:17.000
The merchant's jars are full of oil.

32:17.000 --> 32:20.000
She thought, I'll take some from one of them.

32:20.000 --> 32:24.000
She took her pan and went downstairs.

32:25.000 --> 32:31.000
While she was closing the door, a voice from inside one of the jars said,

32:31.000 --> 32:33.000
Is it time yet?

32:33.000 --> 32:35.000
She was very surprised.

32:35.000 --> 32:39.000
She answered, No, it isn't time yet.

32:39.000 --> 32:42.000
She went to another jar.

32:42.000 --> 32:45.000
A voice said, Is it time yet?

32:45.000 --> 32:48.000
She gave the same answer as before.

32:48.000 --> 32:52.000
She went to the other jars, one by one.

32:52.000 --> 32:58.000
She heard the same question from inside each one, and she gave the same answer.

32:58.000 --> 33:01.000
Only one jar didn't speak.

33:01.000 --> 33:02.000
She opened it.

33:02.000 --> 33:05.000
It was full of oil.

33:05.000 --> 33:09.000
She filled her pan and went back upstairs.

33:09.000 --> 33:12.000
The merchant wants to kill my master.

33:12.000 --> 33:15.000
She thought, I must do something.

33:15.000 --> 33:19.000
She heated the oil on the fire until it was very hot.

33:19.000 --> 33:25.000
Then she went downstairs and poured some of the boiling oil into each of the jars.

33:25.000 --> 33:29.000
Now we are all safe and I can sleep in peace.

33:29.000 --> 33:33.000
Morgana said to herself.

33:33.000 --> 33:37.000
At midnight, the captain came downstairs.

33:37.000 --> 33:40.000
It's time, he whispered.

33:40.000 --> 33:43.000
Nothing happened.

33:43.000 --> 33:46.000
He opened one of the jars and looked inside.

33:47.000 --> 33:49.000
He was horrified.

33:49.000 --> 33:51.000
He looked inside the other jars.

33:51.000 --> 33:54.000
All his men were dead.

33:54.000 --> 33:56.000
Boiled in oil.

33:56.000 --> 33:58.000
Ali Baba is a dangerous man.

33:58.000 --> 34:03.000
He thought, and he ran back to the forest.

34:03.000 --> 34:08.000
Ali Baba saw the jars the next day and asked Morgana.

34:08.000 --> 34:11.000
Why are the merchants jars still here?

34:11.000 --> 34:15.000
Morgana showed him the bodies and the jars.

34:15.000 --> 34:16.000
Well done.

34:16.000 --> 34:19.000
You are a very clever girl.

34:19.000 --> 34:22.000
Ali Baba said.

34:22.000 --> 34:25.000
Many months passed.

34:25.000 --> 34:33.000
The captain changed his name to Kawaja Hussein and bought a shop in the market square.

34:33.000 --> 34:36.000
He sold the cloth and carpets from the cave.

34:36.000 --> 34:40.000
He became friends with the other shopkeepers.

34:40.000 --> 34:43.000
One of them was a young man.

34:43.000 --> 34:47.000
One day, Ali Baba visited the young man's shop.

34:47.000 --> 34:49.000
The captain saw him.

34:49.000 --> 34:52.000
Later, he asked his young friend,

34:52.000 --> 34:55.000
who was that man in your shop today?

34:55.000 --> 34:58.000
That was my father, Ali Baba.

34:58.000 --> 35:00.000
The boy replied.

35:00.000 --> 35:02.000
The captain was surprised.

35:02.000 --> 35:05.000
That's interesting, he thought.

35:05.000 --> 35:08.000
He still wanted to kill Ali Baba.

35:08.000 --> 35:13.000
Some weeks after that, Ali Baba's son went to his father and said,

35:13.000 --> 35:19.000
Father, I would like to invite my friend, Kawaja Hussein, to dinner tomorrow.

35:19.000 --> 35:20.000
Of course.

35:20.000 --> 35:22.000
Replied Ali Baba.

35:22.000 --> 35:26.000
I'll ask Morgana to make something special to eat.

35:26.000 --> 35:31.000
The next evening, the captain arrived at Ali Baba's house.

35:31.000 --> 35:35.000
When Morgana saw him, she said to herself.

35:35.000 --> 35:38.000
This is the merchant who wanted to kill my master.

35:38.000 --> 35:40.000
He has another plot.

35:40.000 --> 35:43.000
I must do something.

35:43.000 --> 35:48.000
She served dinner, and then she put on a very beautiful dress.

35:48.000 --> 35:51.000
She went to the cook and said,

35:51.000 --> 35:54.000
Tonight I'm going to dance for our master's guest,

35:54.000 --> 35:57.000
and you're going to play the tambourine for me.

35:57.000 --> 36:00.000
Come, let's go to them now.

36:00.000 --> 36:04.000
Morgana danced some beautiful dancers.

36:04.000 --> 36:06.000
The last one was very exciting.

36:06.000 --> 36:09.000
She had a dagger in her hand.

36:09.000 --> 36:16.000
After this dance, Morgana took the tambourine from the cook and went to the men.

36:16.000 --> 36:20.000
Both Ali Baba and his son put a gold coin in it.

36:20.000 --> 36:23.000
Then she went to the captain.

36:23.000 --> 36:26.000
He put his hand in his pocket to take out some money.

36:26.000 --> 36:33.000
But just at that moment, Morgana took her dagger and plunged it into his heart.

36:33.000 --> 36:37.000
He fell to the floor, dead.

36:37.000 --> 36:39.000
Ali Baba was shocked.

36:39.000 --> 36:42.000
Morgana, why did you do that?

36:42.000 --> 36:43.000
He said.

36:43.000 --> 36:47.000
He was the captain of the band of thieves, and he wanted to kill you.

36:47.000 --> 36:49.000
She replied.

36:49.000 --> 36:55.000
She lifted the man's jacket and showed Ali Baba the knife in his belt.

36:55.000 --> 36:58.000
You are a very clever woman, Morgana.

36:58.000 --> 37:00.000
He said.

37:00.000 --> 37:04.000
Then he looked at his son and said to him,

37:04.000 --> 37:08.000
Son, you must marry Morgana.

37:08.000 --> 37:14.000
She is the cleverest woman in Persia.

37:14.000 --> 37:21.000
The second voyage of Sinbad the sailor, part one.

37:21.000 --> 37:26.000
There was once a sailor from Baghdad called Sinbad.

37:27.000 --> 37:30.000
He made seven long voyages in his life.

37:30.000 --> 37:34.000
They were all full of adventures.

37:34.000 --> 37:40.000
He met many strange people and saw many strange things.

37:40.000 --> 37:47.000
When he was old, he liked telling people about his adventures and they liked listening.

37:47.000 --> 37:51.000
This is the story of his second voyage.

37:52.000 --> 37:59.000
When I returned home from my first voyage, I lived a comfortable life in the city for some years.

37:59.000 --> 38:01.000
Then I began to get bored.

38:01.000 --> 38:04.000
I dreamt of sailing the seas again.

38:04.000 --> 38:07.000
I wanted new adventures.

38:07.000 --> 38:12.000
One morning I packed my chest and travelled to the port of Basra.

38:12.000 --> 38:17.000
There was a good, strong ship in the harbor and it was ready to sail.

38:17.000 --> 38:19.000
I got on it.

38:19.000 --> 38:24.000
We travelled from port to port and from island to island.

38:24.000 --> 38:31.000
The other passengers on the ship were merchants and when we stopped they bought and sold things.

38:31.000 --> 38:34.000
Soon I began to do the same.

38:34.000 --> 38:40.000
Weeks and months passed pleasantly but without adventure.

38:40.000 --> 38:47.000
Then one day the wind took our ship to a strange and beautiful island.

38:47.000 --> 38:54.000
There were trees with delicious fruit, flowers of many colours and streams of sweet water.

38:54.000 --> 39:01.000
The air was full of the songs of birds but there weren't any people.

39:01.000 --> 39:05.000
The other passengers started to explore the island.

39:05.000 --> 39:09.000
I was tired so I sat under a tree.

39:09.000 --> 39:17.000
I ate some of the delicious fruit from the trees and drank some of the sweet water from the streams.

39:17.000 --> 39:20.000
Then I fell asleep.

39:20.000 --> 39:23.000
When I woke up I looked around.

39:23.000 --> 39:26.000
I was alone on the island.

39:26.000 --> 39:30.000
I looked out to sea and saw my ship on the horizon.

39:30.000 --> 39:33.000
I began to feel afraid.

39:33.000 --> 39:39.000
Oh, poor me! I said, what shall I do now?

39:39.000 --> 39:43.000
I walked around the island for an hour or more.

39:43.000 --> 39:46.000
Then I climbed a tall tree.

39:46.000 --> 39:52.000
I can get a better view of the island from the top of a tree, I thought.

39:52.000 --> 40:01.000
I looked left and right but I saw only trees, flowers, birds, the sea and the sky.

40:01.000 --> 40:04.000
Then I looked more carefully.

40:04.000 --> 40:09.000
There was a big white object in the distance.

40:09.000 --> 40:12.000
I decided to go and have a look at it.

40:12.000 --> 40:17.000
When I got nearer I saw that it was a dome.

40:17.000 --> 40:20.000
I touched it and walked around it.

40:20.000 --> 40:28.000
It was very smooth and very big but there were no doors or windows in it.

40:28.000 --> 40:31.000
Suddenly it became dark.

40:31.000 --> 40:35.000
I looked up and saw an enormous bird above me.

40:35.000 --> 40:37.000
It covered the sun.

40:37.000 --> 40:39.000
A rock!

40:39.000 --> 40:45.000
I said to myself, and this white dome is her egg.

40:45.000 --> 40:48.000
I remembered a traveler's story about these birds.

40:48.000 --> 40:53.000
It said that rocks caught elephants for their babies to eat.

40:54.000 --> 41:01.000
Just at that moment the bird landed on top of her egg and soon she was asleep.

41:01.000 --> 41:09.000
I quickly took off my turban and tied one end of it to the rock's foot and the other around my waist.

41:09.000 --> 41:16.000
Perhaps this bird will take me to a land where there are cities and people, I thought.

41:16.000 --> 41:19.000
I waited all night.

41:19.000 --> 41:25.000
In the morning the rock woke up and flew away and she took me with her.

41:25.000 --> 41:28.000
She didn't take me very far.

41:28.000 --> 41:31.000
We landed on the side of a mountain.

41:31.000 --> 41:37.000
I quickly untied my turban and hid behind a rock.

41:37.000 --> 41:43.000
The rock picked up a huge snake in its talons and flew away.

41:43.000 --> 41:45.000
I looked around me.

41:45.000 --> 41:48.000
I saw a lot more snakes.

41:48.000 --> 41:51.000
They were sleeping among the rocks.

41:51.000 --> 41:56.000
This is a terrible place, I thought.

41:56.000 --> 42:06.000
There was fruit to eat and water to drink on the island, but there are only snakes here.

42:06.000 --> 42:09.000
Listening activity

42:09.000 --> 42:16.000
The island of Sri Lanka is in the Indian Ocean, southeast of India.

42:16.000 --> 42:24.000
It is shaped like a big pair with the small part in the north and the large part in the south.

42:24.000 --> 42:34.000
The greatest length is 440 kilometers and the greatest width is 220 kilometers.

42:34.000 --> 42:39.000
The largest city, Colombo, is on the west coast.

42:39.000 --> 42:44.000
The port town of Trinko Mali is on the northeast coast.

42:44.000 --> 42:49.000
It has one of the best natural harbors in the world.

42:49.000 --> 42:52.000
Gal is another port town.

42:52.000 --> 42:55.000
It is on the southwest coast.

42:55.000 --> 43:01.000
In the south-central part of the island there are many high mountains.

43:01.000 --> 43:06.000
The highest mountain is Mount Peduro Talagala.

43:06.000 --> 43:11.000
It is 2524 meters high.

43:11.000 --> 43:15.000
In the north the land is flat and dry.

43:15.000 --> 43:22.000
There are many rivers and streams in Sri Lanka, especially in the south-central region.

43:22.000 --> 43:27.000
The longest river is the Mahaweli Ganga.

43:27.000 --> 43:31.000
It is 335 kilometers long.

43:31.000 --> 43:40.000
It starts in the mountains in the south-central region and empties into the Indian Ocean south of Trinko Mali.

43:41.000 --> 43:46.000
Part 2

43:46.000 --> 43:49.000
I walked down into the valley.

43:49.000 --> 43:54.000
There weren't any trees or flowers, only sand and rocks.

43:54.000 --> 43:59.000
The small stones under my feet sparkled in the sunshine.

43:59.000 --> 44:02.000
I looked at them more carefully.

44:02.000 --> 44:05.000
They weren't stones.

44:05.000 --> 44:07.000
They were diamonds.

44:08.000 --> 44:11.000
Then I knew where I was.

44:11.000 --> 44:16.000
This is the valley of diamonds, I said to myself.

44:16.000 --> 44:19.000
Nobody escapes from here.

44:19.000 --> 44:23.000
I began to feel very afraid.

44:23.000 --> 44:25.000
I looked around.

44:25.000 --> 44:28.000
The snakes were still asleep among the rocks.

44:28.000 --> 44:33.000
Their bodies were as thick as tree trunks.

44:33.000 --> 44:39.000
They'll wake up when it is dark, I thought, and come out to look for food.

44:39.000 --> 44:43.000
I must find a safe place to sleep tonight.

44:43.000 --> 44:46.000
Perhaps there are some caves here.

44:46.000 --> 44:51.000
It was beginning to get dark and I could hear the snakes.

44:51.000 --> 44:53.000
They were waking up.

44:53.000 --> 44:56.000
I walked faster.

44:56.000 --> 44:58.000
Soon I found a cave.

44:58.000 --> 45:03.000
It was big and dark inside, but the floor was dry.

45:03.000 --> 45:07.000
This is a good place to sleep, I thought.

45:07.000 --> 45:13.000
I'll put a big rock in the mouth of the cave to keep the snakes out.

45:13.000 --> 45:17.000
I'll be safe here until the morning.

45:17.000 --> 45:20.000
I went in and looked around.

45:20.000 --> 45:25.000
At the back of the cave I could see two small red lights.

45:25.000 --> 45:28.000
Two eyes.

45:28.000 --> 45:31.000
There was a huge snake there.

45:31.000 --> 45:34.000
She was sitting on her eggs.

45:34.000 --> 45:36.000
She was looking at me.

45:36.000 --> 45:39.000
I ran out of the cave.

45:39.000 --> 45:45.000
It was completely dark in the valley now and the snakes in the rocks were coming out.

45:45.000 --> 45:48.000
They made a terrible noise.

45:48.000 --> 45:50.000
I was very afraid.

45:50.000 --> 45:54.000
I decided to stay in the cave.

45:54.000 --> 45:58.000
One snake is better than a hundred, I thought,

45:58.000 --> 46:03.000
and she is more interested in her eggs than she is in me.

46:03.000 --> 46:08.000
So I found a rock and closed the cave.

46:08.000 --> 46:10.000
I was awake all night.

46:10.000 --> 46:13.000
I could hear the snakes outside.

46:13.000 --> 46:15.000
The noise was terrible.

46:15.000 --> 46:21.000
The snake at the back of the cave sat on her eggs and looked at me.

46:22.000 --> 46:27.000
When I saw the first light from the sun I moved the rock and went out.

46:27.000 --> 46:29.000
It was quiet.

46:29.000 --> 46:36.000
The snakes were asleep so I left the cave and started walking down the valley.

46:36.000 --> 46:41.000
Suddenly something fell out of the sky and landed at my feet.

46:41.000 --> 46:44.000
It was a big piece of meat.

46:44.000 --> 46:48.000
Then another piece of meat fell out of the sky.

46:48.000 --> 46:56.000
I was very surprised, but I remembered another traveler's story about the valley of diamonds.

46:56.000 --> 47:03.000
The story said that diamond merchants never came into the valley because it was a very dangerous place,

47:03.000 --> 47:08.000
but they had a very clever way of getting the diamonds out.

47:08.000 --> 47:15.000
They stood on the tops of the mountains and threw big pieces of meat down into the valley.

47:15.000 --> 47:21.000
The meat was soft so the precious stones stuck to it.

47:21.000 --> 47:26.000
At midday rocks and eagles flew down into the valley.

47:26.000 --> 47:32.000
They picked up the pieces of meat and carried them up to the tops of the mountains.

47:32.000 --> 47:39.000
When the birds landed the merchants shouted loudly and made a lot of noise.

47:39.000 --> 47:43.000
The birds were afraid and flew away.

47:43.000 --> 47:50.000
Then the merchants took the diamonds out of the meat and put them into chests.

47:50.000 --> 47:55.000
This was the only way of getting the diamonds out of the valley.

47:55.000 --> 48:02.000
Later the merchants sold the precious stones in the cities for a lot of money.

48:02.000 --> 48:05.000
The story gave me an idea.

48:05.000 --> 48:09.000
I filled my pockets with the biggest diamonds I could find.

48:09.000 --> 48:14.000
Then I tied myself to a piece of meat with my turban.

48:14.000 --> 48:18.000
Soon an eagle came down.

48:18.000 --> 48:25.000
It picked up the piece of meat and me and flew up to the top of a mountain with it.

48:25.000 --> 48:30.000
As soon as we landed there was a lot of noise and shouting.

48:30.000 --> 48:33.000
The bird was afraid and flew away.

48:33.000 --> 48:37.000
I untied myself quickly and started to run.

48:37.000 --> 48:40.000
Hey, you stop!

48:40.000 --> 48:42.000
A man shouted.

48:42.000 --> 48:44.000
I stopped.

48:44.000 --> 48:45.000
Don't hurt me, sir.

48:45.000 --> 48:48.000
I said, I'm an honest man.

48:48.000 --> 48:51.000
I don't want your diamonds.

48:51.000 --> 48:55.000
I took three big diamonds out of my pocket.

48:55.000 --> 48:58.000
Look, I said, take these.

48:58.000 --> 49:04.000
I picked them up in the valley and I gave him the stones.

49:04.000 --> 49:08.000
The man was very happy and thanked me.

49:08.000 --> 49:10.000
He took me to meet his friends.

49:10.000 --> 49:13.000
They were all diamond merchants.

49:13.000 --> 49:18.000
They gave me food and drink and listened to my story.

49:18.000 --> 49:26.000
One of them said, you're the first man to escape from this valley.

49:26.000 --> 49:29.000
I traveled with them for many weeks.

49:29.000 --> 49:34.000
We visited many countries and we had many adventures.

49:34.000 --> 49:40.000
I gave them diamonds and they gave me food and drink.

49:40.000 --> 49:44.000
In one port there was a ship that was going to Basra.

49:44.000 --> 49:51.000
I was tired of traveling and I wanted to see my family again, so I got on it.

49:51.000 --> 49:55.000
From Basra I traveled back to Baghdad.

49:55.000 --> 49:59.000
I was happy to be home again.

49:59.000 --> 50:01.000
I was a rich man.

50:01.000 --> 50:07.000
I gave many presents to my family and money to the poor people of the city.

50:07.000 --> 50:11.000
I enjoyed my comfortable life at home.

50:11.000 --> 50:15.000
But after a few years I started to get bored.

50:15.000 --> 50:24.000
I wanted to travel the seas again and have new adventures.

50:24.000 --> 50:29.000
The story of the young king of the Black Islands.

50:29.000 --> 50:32.000
Part 1.

50:32.000 --> 50:39.000
When King Mahmoud of the Black Islands died, his young son became king.

50:39.000 --> 50:43.000
A few weeks later he married his cousin.

50:43.000 --> 50:49.000
The young king loved his wife very much and he thought that she loved him.

50:49.000 --> 50:51.000
He was happy.

50:51.000 --> 50:56.000
But she was not a good wife and she didn't love him.

50:56.000 --> 51:00.000
She also had magic powers.

51:00.000 --> 51:05.000
The king and the queen lived happily for five years.

51:05.000 --> 51:11.000
Then one afternoon the young king heard a conversation between two of his wife's maids.

51:11.000 --> 51:15.000
They didn't know that he was listening to them.

51:15.000 --> 51:18.000
It's sad that the queen doesn't love the king, isn't it?

51:18.000 --> 51:20.000
One of them said.

51:20.000 --> 51:21.000
Yes it is.

51:21.000 --> 51:23.000
The other maid replied.

51:23.000 --> 51:25.000
She's a bad woman.

51:25.000 --> 51:29.000
Every night she puts a sleeping potion in his wine.

51:29.000 --> 51:34.000
Then when he is asleep she goes out to meet her lover in the forest.

51:34.000 --> 51:37.000
The young king was horrified.

51:37.000 --> 51:41.000
He decided to watch his wife carefully.

51:42.000 --> 51:50.000
That night he didn't drink his wine so he wasn't asleep when the queen got out of bed and left the palace.

51:50.000 --> 51:52.000
He followed her to the forest.

51:52.000 --> 51:57.000
Her lover was there and they kissed passionately.

51:57.000 --> 52:01.000
When the young king saw them together he was very angry.

52:01.000 --> 52:05.000
He took out his sword and hit the man on the neck.

52:05.000 --> 52:08.000
The man fell to the ground.

52:08.000 --> 52:15.000
Then the young king ran back to the palace before the queen had time to see his face.

52:15.000 --> 52:19.000
The next morning the queen came to his room.

52:19.000 --> 52:24.000
She was wearing black clothes and she was crying.

52:24.000 --> 52:25.000
Husband?

52:25.000 --> 52:26.000
She said.

52:26.000 --> 52:34.000
I'm mourning my family, my father, my mother and my two brothers are all dead.

52:34.000 --> 52:37.000
The young king said nothing.

52:37.000 --> 52:41.000
He knew that it was not true.

52:41.000 --> 52:43.000
The queen mourned for a year.

52:43.000 --> 52:52.000
At the end of this time she built a black dome in the palace garden and filmed it with precious carpets and paintings.

52:52.000 --> 52:55.000
Then she took her lover's body there.

52:55.000 --> 53:00.000
He wasn't dead but he couldn't move or speak.

53:00.000 --> 53:06.000
She put him on a sofa in a dark room and built a beautiful fountain for him there.

53:06.000 --> 53:11.000
She went to see him every day and gave him soup and wine to drink.

53:11.000 --> 53:15.000
She cried all the time.

53:15.000 --> 53:18.000
Three years passed.

53:18.000 --> 53:23.000
One day the young king went to the dome to speak to his wife.

53:23.000 --> 53:25.000
She was crying as usual.

53:25.000 --> 53:27.000
He was very angry.

53:27.000 --> 53:30.000
I'm tired of your tears.

53:30.000 --> 53:33.000
He shouted and he took out his sword.

53:33.000 --> 53:35.000
You're a bad woman.

53:35.000 --> 53:37.000
I know that you keep your lover here.

53:37.000 --> 53:39.000
Yes, I do.

53:39.000 --> 53:40.000
The queen replied.

53:40.000 --> 53:43.000
I love him and I hate you.

53:43.000 --> 53:46.000
The king lifted his sword to kill her.

53:46.000 --> 53:50.000
But the queen put a magic spell on him before he could hit her.

53:50.000 --> 53:55.000
She turned his legs into a block of black marble.

53:55.000 --> 53:58.000
He couldn't move.

53:58.000 --> 54:02.000
Then she turned the four islands into four mountains.

54:02.000 --> 54:11.000
The city into a lake and the people in the city into fish.

54:11.000 --> 54:14.000
Part two.

54:14.000 --> 54:19.000
After that the queen visited the black dome every day.

54:19.000 --> 54:25.000
First she went to her husband and beat him one hundred times with a whip.

54:25.000 --> 54:28.000
He cried and shouted loudly.

54:28.000 --> 54:31.000
But her heart was hard.

54:31.000 --> 54:34.000
Then she went to her lover.

54:34.000 --> 54:37.000
After giving him some soup and wine she said,

54:37.000 --> 54:39.000
How are you today my love?

54:39.000 --> 54:41.000
Speak to me.

54:41.000 --> 54:45.000
But he never moved and he never spoke.

54:45.000 --> 54:51.000
Some years later a king from a distant country traveled to the black islands.

54:51.000 --> 54:56.000
He went in the black dome and found the young king.

54:56.000 --> 55:01.000
When he heard his story he felt very sorry for him.

55:01.000 --> 55:03.000
He promised to help him.

55:03.000 --> 55:05.000
I have a plan.

55:05.000 --> 55:07.000
He said.

55:07.000 --> 55:12.000
The next day the king went to the room where the queen's lover was.

55:12.000 --> 55:17.000
He killed him with his sword and threw the body down a deep well.

55:17.000 --> 55:20.000
Then he lay down on the sofa.

55:20.000 --> 55:23.000
Soon the queen arrived.

55:23.000 --> 55:28.000
She went to her husband and beat him one hundred times.

55:28.000 --> 55:32.000
After that she went to her lover's room.

55:32.000 --> 55:37.000
It was dark so she couldn't see the man on the sofa very well.

55:37.000 --> 55:40.000
How are you today my love?

55:40.000 --> 55:41.000
She said.

55:41.000 --> 55:43.000
Speak to me.

55:43.000 --> 55:45.000
The king answered.

55:45.000 --> 55:47.000
I'm very tired.

55:47.000 --> 55:53.000
When you beat your husband he shouts very loudly and I can't sleep.

55:53.000 --> 55:55.000
Take the spell off.

55:55.000 --> 55:58.000
I don't want to hear him anymore.

55:58.000 --> 56:02.000
The queen was very happy to hear her lover's voice again.

56:02.000 --> 56:03.000
She said,

56:03.000 --> 56:06.000
I'll take the spell off immediately my love.

56:06.000 --> 56:12.000
She went back to her husband's room and took a cup of water which she heated on a fire.

56:12.000 --> 56:18.000
Then she said some magic words and threw the water over the block of marble.

56:18.000 --> 56:20.000
Now you are free.

56:20.000 --> 56:21.000
She said.

56:21.000 --> 56:24.000
Go away from here and never come back.

56:24.000 --> 56:30.000
The young king jumped for joy and the queen went back to her lover's room.

56:30.000 --> 56:32.000
My husband is free.

56:32.000 --> 56:33.000
She said.

56:33.000 --> 56:35.000
Are you better now my love?

56:35.000 --> 56:37.000
The king answered.

56:37.000 --> 56:39.000
I'm still tired.

56:39.000 --> 56:45.000
Every night at midnight the fish in the lake jump out of the water and cry and shout loudly.

56:45.000 --> 56:47.000
I can't sleep.

56:47.000 --> 56:49.000
Take the spell off.

56:49.000 --> 56:52.000
I don't want to hear them anymore.

56:52.000 --> 56:57.000
The queen immediately ran to the lake and took the spell off.

56:57.000 --> 57:03.000
The fish became men, women and children again and the lake became a city.

57:03.000 --> 57:07.000
The queen went back to her lover's room and said.

57:07.000 --> 57:09.000
The people are free.

57:09.000 --> 57:11.000
Do you feel better now?

57:11.000 --> 57:14.000
Come here, said the king.

57:14.000 --> 57:17.000
Come closer.

57:17.000 --> 57:19.000
The queen moved closer.

57:19.000 --> 57:25.000
Then the king suddenly jumped up and cut her body in half with his sword.

57:25.000 --> 57:28.000
The queen is dead, he said to the young king.

57:28.000 --> 57:31.000
And your city and your people are free.

57:31.000 --> 57:34.000
The young king was very happy.

57:34.000 --> 57:37.000
Why don't you come back with me to my country?

57:37.000 --> 57:38.000
Ask the king.

57:38.000 --> 57:40.000
I have no children of my own.

57:40.000 --> 57:43.000
You can be my son and rule my kingdom when I die.

57:43.000 --> 57:45.000
Thank you, I will.

57:45.000 --> 57:47.000
Replied the young king immediately.

57:47.000 --> 57:50.000
I never want to leave you.

57:50.000 --> 57:52.000
Good, said the king.

57:52.000 --> 57:55.000
I'll send my vizier to the Black Islands.

57:55.000 --> 57:58.000
He'll be a good sultan.

57:59.000 --> 58:06.000
So the two kings made preparations for their long journey back to the king's country.

58:06.000 --> 58:13.000
They arrived safely and they both lived peacefully for the rest of their lives.

58:28.000 --> 58:31.000
Thank you.

